The paper discusses the use of automated negotiation in Ambient Intelligence domains, which involves the interaction between people and systems. This falls under the category of Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI). The negotiation model proposed in the paper involves multiple agents with complex utility functions, which is a topic of interest in Multi-Agent Systems (cs.MA). The use of genetic algorithms and computational optimization techniques also suggests a connection to Machine Learning (cs.LG) and Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science (cs.CE). Finally, the negotiation model is designed to operate in complex environments with multiple agents, which falls under the category of Systems and Control (cs.SY).
